OK, thank you.

00:49:05.212 --> 00:49:08.056
[APPLAUSE]

00:49:11.380 --> 00:49:15.537
PHILIP TAN: OK, I'm going
to turn the volume down.

00:49:15.537 --> 00:49:17.245
What's working for
this game's aesthetic?

00:49:20.690 --> 00:49:23.385
Did I see a hand back there?

00:49:23.385 --> 00:49:24.870
Yeah, right there.

00:49:24.870 --> 00:49:26.602
STUDENT: We're all
really used to games

00:49:26.602 --> 00:49:29.562
with cylindrical coordinates
through a camera.

00:49:29.562 --> 00:49:31.740
And this game appeared
to have it be the case

00:49:31.740 --> 00:49:34.297
that as you look down, one
can then rotate your camera.

00:49:34.297 --> 00:49:36.338
It really felt like you're
looking straight down.

00:49:36.338 --> 00:49:38.758
And so we're very used to
having cylindrical coordinates.

00:49:38.758 --> 00:49:39.995
PHILIP TAN: Mhm, yeah.

00:49:39.995 --> 00:49:44.810
This is a game that uses sort
of WASD first person controls.

00:49:44.810 --> 00:49:48.462
Only first of all,
you're not carrying a gun

00:49:48.462 --> 00:49:49.670
and looking around like that.

00:49:49.670 --> 00:49:52.130
You're pretty much doing
this for the entire game.

00:49:52.130 --> 00:49:58.080
So you're always kind of
rotating around your center.

00:49:58.080 --> 00:50:01.554
So that's a
systemic-- essentially

00:50:01.554 --> 00:50:02.470
how the controls work.

00:50:02.470 --> 00:50:04.595
STUDENT: Checkpoint restart
happened really, really

00:50:04.595 --> 00:50:06.680
fast when you screwed up.

00:50:06.680 --> 00:50:09.710
PHILIP TAN: Yeah, yeah, so it's
like, survive to this point,

00:50:09.710 --> 00:50:12.140
get to the next checkpoint.

00:50:12.140 --> 00:50:14.250
And things are actually
flying past you

00:50:14.250 --> 00:50:16.670
at a pretty high rate as well.

00:50:16.670 --> 00:50:17.610
What else?

00:50:21.840 --> 00:50:22.860
Music?

00:50:22.860 --> 00:50:24.331
Art?

00:50:24.331 --> 00:50:24.830
Storyline?

00:50:28.847 --> 00:50:29.680
STUDENT: [INAUDIBLE]

00:50:35.985 --> 00:50:37.655
PHILIP TAN: I think
the music-- does

00:50:37.655 --> 00:50:41.540
it start the moment your foot
leaves the first building?

00:50:41.540 --> 00:50:43.690
I think there are
some levels where

00:50:43.690 --> 00:50:46.147
it does that, where the
music only starts the moment

00:50:46.147 --> 00:50:47.230
you jump off the building.

00:50:47.230 --> 00:50:48.570
It's like, you can stay
